HEADWORD: Oscitancy
<hw>Os"ci*tan*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Oscitant</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of gaping or yawning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Drowsiness; dullness; sluggishness.</def>
<rj><au>Hallam.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It might proceed from the <qex>oscitancy</qex> of
transcribers.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oscitant</ent>⟦br⟧
